<section id="workflows" class="install-section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflows</p>
    <h2>A typed DAG, authored in HCL.</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      Compose deterministic commands, agent loops, HTTP calls, custom
      tools, and fan-outs into a single graph. References between steps
      make data flow visible in the file, and <code>condukt check</code>
      validates the graph before it runs.
    </p>
    <div class="code-block">{% highlight "hcl" %}workflow "release_notes" {
  runtime {
    model = "openai:gpt-4.1-mini"
  }

  cmd "version" {
    argv = ["sh", "-c", "git describe --tags --always"]
  }

  agent "draft" {
    needs = ["version"]
    input = "Draft release notes for ${task.version.stdout}"
  }

  output = task.draft.output
}{% endhighlight %}</div>
    <p>
      Five step kinds compose any workflow: <code>cmd</code>,
      <code>agent</code>, <code>http</code>, <code>tool</code>, and
      <code>map</code>. Run with <code>condukt run release_notes.hcl</code>
      or validate without executing using <code>condukt check release_notes.hcl</code>.
      <a href="https://hexdocs.pm/condukt/workflows.html">Read the workflows guide</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="install" class="install-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Two ways to run Condukt</h2>
    <div class="mode-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>Library</h3>
        <p>Use Hex when agents should run inside your Elixir app and share
        your supervision tree.</p>
        <div class="code-block">{% highlight "elixir" %}def deps do
  [{:condukt, "~> 0.13"}]
end{% endhighlight %}</div>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Engine</h3>
        <p>Use mise when you want the standalone workflow runner with Erlang
        and Condukt bundled into one executable.</p>
        <div class="code-block">{% highlight "bash" %}mise use -g github:tuist/condukt
condukt check hello.hcl{% endhighlight %}</div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <ol class="steps">
      <li>
        <h3>Define an agent</h3>
        <div class="code-block">{% highlight "elixir" %}defmodule MyApp.CodingAgent do
  use Condukt

  @impl true
  def tools, do: Condukt.Tools.coding_tools()
end{% endhighlight %}</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Run it</h3>
        <div class="code-block">{% highlight "elixir" %}{:ok, agent} = MyApp.CodingAgent.start_link(
  api_key: System.get_env("ANTHROPIC_API_KEY")
)

{:ok, response} = Condukt.run(agent, "Refactor this module."){% endhighlight %}</div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
